etf df columns
['Symbol', 'Name', '', 'Price', 'Change', 'Change %', 'Volume', '50 DayAverage', '200 DayAverage', '3 Month Return', 'YTD Return', '52 WkChange %', '52 Wk Range']

stock df columns
['Symbol', 'Name', '', 'Price', 'Change', 'Change %', 'Volume', 'Avg Vol (3M)', 'Market Cap', 'P/E Ratio(TTM)', '52 WkChange %', '52 Wk Range']

You might also consider dynamic weighting, e.g., adjusting weights based on market conditions:
Bull markets → more momentum
Bear markets → more quality

2️⃣ Ignore index.html changes on other branches
After creating a branch:
# Example: create a new feature branch
git checkout -b feature-branch

# Tell Git to ignore local changes to index.html on this branch
git update-index --assume-unchanged index.html

